You are building Miomika — a voice AI companion app for Thai creators.

PRODUCT: A kawaii cat companion named Miomi that helps users create social media content through voice conversation. The pet emotional bond is the core product.

TECH STACK:
- Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, App Router
- Supabase for database and auth
- Claude API (Haiku for free users, Sonnet for paid)
- Web Speech API for voice (free, browser-native)
- Framer Motion for Miomi animations

DESIGN RULES — NEVER BREAK THESE:
- Background always #FFFFFF, never colored
- Rose accent #8B1A35 for buttons and active states
- Gold #B8860B for premium and level badges
- Miomi always free on white canvas — NO frames, NO circles, NO containers around her
- Mobile-first, every screen designed for 375px width first
- Bottom tab navigation — Home, Create, Dashboard, Friends, Me
- NEVER use generic AI emojis or standard Unicode emojis anywhere in the UI. No 🐱 🐶 ✨ 💕 🌸 or any standard emoji. Every visual element must feel Miomika branded and unique. Use Miomika's own character assets, custom icons, or text only. If an icon is needed use lucide-react icons only. This rule applies to all UI text, buttons, labels, speech bubbles, and messages.

CODE RULES:
- Always use TypeScript, never plain JavaScript
- Always use Tailwind classes, never inline styles
- Component files in /components folder
- Page files in /app folder following Next.js App Router structure
- All Supabase calls in /lib/supabase folder
- All API routes in /app/api folder
- Environment variables never hardcoded, always from .env.local

CURRENT PHASE: Phase 1 MVP — Week 1
Building: Project structure, Supabase schema, auth, home screen with Miomi
